      "writtenOn": "2019-02-02T02:15:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "how about this?\n\nIn Tast, tests either pass (by reporting zero errors) or fail (by reporting one or more errors). If a test requires functionality that isn\u0027t provided by the DUT, the test is skipped automatically rather than being executed.\n\nAvoid writing tests that probe the DUT\u0027s capabilities at runtime, e.g.\n\n```go\n// WRONG: ...\nfunc MyTest(...) {\n    if !supports720PCamera() {\n        s.Log(...)\n        return\n    }\n    // ...\n```",
      "parentUuid": "32d87fdb_fa8363db",
